This repository is a deployment-focused fork of Aave V3
(https://github.com/aave-dao/aave-v3-origin, v3.6.0), adapted to deploy
against Rome Protocol's SPL_ERC20_cached token wrappers on an EVM chain
running natively inside the Solana runtime.

Licensing is preserved from upstream on a per-file basis (see SPDX
headers and LICENSE): core protocol contracts remain under the Business
Source License 1.1 (BUSL-1.1) as published by Aave DAO; periphery and
interface files retain their original MIT / LGPL-3.0 licenses. The
BUSL-1.1 terms, including the Change Date and Additional Use Grant, are
those set by the upstream licensor (Aave DAO) — this fork adds no new
grants and removes no restrictions.

Modifications relative to upstream are limited to deployment scripts,
token-wrapper integration, and configuration for Rome chains.
